Cyricus if he doesn't he should because he is right. Beastlords do not need balanced against magicians. I appreciate your interest in our class but your approval or disapproval of changes needs to be considered irrelevant by verant and the beastlord community. We are priest/melee hybrids and should be balanced against other priests, melees, and hybrids.<br>
<br>
That isn't to say I don't personally value anyone's input but this constant BS arguement of how beastlord pets need to be tougher or weaker because of what happens/has happened to magicians or necromancers needs to end.<br>
<br>
BEASTLORDS WILL NEVER HAVE DPS LIKE A NUKING MAGICIAN AND PET. Please give up now. It will never, ever, ever, happen. Beastlords should be balanced against other melees as either a defensive tank, offensive tank, or group support role. Our skill set suggests offensive tank with some group support similar to rangers so it seems reasonable to suggest combined BL/pet damage should be about the same as a similarly equipped ranger going all out for damage, and probably a bit under a warrior when we can't use our pet. What that means verant can figure out in thier spiffy damage simulator that tookd 3 tries to figure out 2handed weapon balance  <br>
<br>
--Kreseth <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Kreseth I agree our overall balance should be against other Offensive Melee, Rangers, Rogues and Monks.  Actually since we are a Hybrid we should primarily in terms of utility and DPS be judged against Rangers.   Weighing in our Weaker AC and defense we should be doing slightly better DPS wise then a Ranger.  That DPS should be us plus our Warder.  Check out this thread here from a couple of weeks ago on the Rangers Glade (<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://forums.interealms.com/ranger/showthread.php?s=7952f078a0cf723d381d8125536c2287&threadid=9142).">forums.interealms.com/ran...did=9142).</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END-->  You will see that in normal XP situations we are close to where we want to be in that regards. I know I can show you a ton of parses if you want them of a non-epic 56-58 BL getting between me and my warder 50-70DPS, that thread shows Epic Rangers in the 45-55DPS range.  Where we aren't even close is in raid situations, fully buffed where if I'm lucky and can have my warder up I still get that same 50-70DPS even Enchanter hasted, the Ranger is getting 80-100DPS. Haste just means so much more to Ranger then to us due to Dual Attack.  None of this takes into account the Ranger Discipline Trueshot, that while situational is far superior to any discipline we have.  Yes there is futher balancing that needs to be done here, but it is actually not that far from where it should be.<br>
<br>
However, that said, Comparisons of our Warder to Mage pets is not unwarranted as well.  Pet to Pet comparisons only.  Comparison of Warders to Necro Pets is also not uncalled for.  What we should be avoiding in those discussions are comparisons that compare Mage + Pet , Necro + Pet and Beastlord + Pet since Mages, Necros and Beastlords overall roles are completely different.   Why pet to pet, for the same reason you compare Rangers to Warriors to Rogues to Monks to etc.,   They have the same basic capabilities,  tanking and DPS.  Therfore they need to be balances to one another.<br>
<br>
Also I'd like to thank all the mages that have contributed to this thread.  This is the most civil converstation we have had yet between our two classes and I very much enjoy reading threads where the quality of information is so much higher then the quality of whinning.  I had avoided this thread to this point because I assumed it had turned into the type of pig headed my pet should be better arguments that all previous threads had.  Cudos to Mages and Beastlords both for keeping this thread at least civil and educational. <p><a target="new" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=250421 ">Cheetira Thunderkatt</a><br>
