<br>
   I then took that information and built a single math function that reduced the swings per roung by 50%, modified the base delay by each classes best haste per level.   This produced a hits per minute number.<br>
<br>
   I took the hits per minute and multiplied that by the max damage for each pet per level, this gave me roughly 50% or maximum possible damage.  This gave me a damage per minute.<br>
<br>
 I then divided the DPM by 60 to come up with a high average DPS which I further reduced to 65%.<br>
<br>
   The idea was to get in the ball park of what normal parsings show for predictive purposes. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=337255">Investigator Aaeorn</A>, Fiftieth Circle Redeemed Thief Catcher of Xev.<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67241">Apprentice Kaatt</A>, Fifty-One Year Old Khati Sha Primalist of Xev.<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=362220">Aaeorm</A>, Enchantement Technician of the Twenty-Fifth Tier of Xev.<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/uyanbun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yanbun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Beastling</span><br>  Posts: 48<br> <font color=#FF9933>(10/5/02 8:58:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3675.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages &amp; Beastlords... what is the best pet?</span><hr size=1> Mage Pets, Necro Pets, and Bst pets, they are all completely different.<br>
<br>
First off, the Beastlord only gets 1 pet. This means it has to be a generalist, a good damage dealer and a good tank. It is that. <br>
<br>
Necro pets, they are supposed to be situational. Many Necros do not use pets when soloing, but they do have their uses, especially in groups and raids. They do damage, but can't really take it.<br>
<br>
Mages get 4 pets. They each have their situational uses. Earth pet is our tank, used for soloing and chaincasting. Firepet is our wizard, used in groups for it's chain stunning. Air pet doesn't have much of a use, its also a generalist. Good for stuns when you want damage along with it (fire pet does crap for damage). Water pet is our rogue. It is there to deal damage, like a Necro pet. It backstabs for over 200. <br>
<br>
Beastlords get tons of spells to augment and enhance their pets. Necros get spells that weaken or possess the mob so their pet can do it's work. Mages don't get much in the way of spells to help out pets out. Nor do we have any alternative if our pet dies, we have to gate or run.<br>
<br>
If our pet dies, even if the mob is at 10% hp, a Mage has to run. We have no root, snare, slow, mez, ect to let us finish it off. We cannot kite without a pet up. Necros can feign death, root, fear, snare, ect. Beastlords can slow and finish the mob off with melee. <p>"History is just a set of lies agreed upon" - Emperor Napoleon Bonaparte
