<br>
If you have a mob at 10% life (which wont run due to low life) Im not sure if I could take it without pets damage. If it isnt lower than a DB mob it would be a gamble.<br>
<br>
In most cases if I have to take an xp mob down 10% without pet I just say forget it, cast FoL once and then run like h--l towards zone.<br>
<br>
The reason is simple, I have heals for myself, but while trying to channel that slow cast I wont deal damage and will still be loosing a lot of hps. I have weapons but I only do 1/2 to 1/3 of my pets damage, with the bugged/old warders the ratio was better on higher levels but generally 1/2 - 1/3 applies, this means that the time it took to bring that mob down 1/2 bub would be double or trippled.<br>
<br>
<br>
Besides that the slow is a necessity for us, I would never wait on casting the slow unless the mob is green or cant be slowed. And its only 30%, your DSs are better to shorten fights than the slow would be (in fact I have a DS potion in my inventory incase of emergencies).<br>
<br>
<br>
The only pet class that has a good chance of surviving without a pet is the Necro since they have a myriad of options to finish the mob without pet or to get out of harms way with a quick cast.<br>
<br>
In the case of Mage Vs Beastlord beastlords would have the best chance of surviving in an out door zone where we can have sow on, in an indoor zone mages have the best chance of surviving with gate. Note that there are some zones that are outdoors that would be even worse than a dungeon for beastlords, TD and OOT for instance.<br>
<br>
<br>
Mages and beastlords are equally pet dependant, and trying to claim we are not by pointing out sow, slow or melee capabilities is silly, mages has spells and capabilities that match ours very well in those aspects. And saying we have spells to augment our pets damage is also an interesting statement, we are forced to use all our pet buffs if our pet would be operational, not using them is like a mage that wont use DS or give their pets weapons, if not worse than that even. And you do get lots of nice buffs for your pet too. You get haste for him, you get DS and you can summon weapons for him. The only spell we have that you dont have an equivalent of is Flash of Light and Im sure you can get it if you complain loud enough of how crippled you are without it.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
I have no interest in getting a better pet than mages, but just to turn around your own arguments:<br>
<br>
Mages get 4 pets, you can choose the one for the right situation. If you group you can choose the water pet for back stabs or the fire pet for stuns, we have to do with our one and only warder. If you solo you can use earth pet and chain nuke or you can use the air pet if you wont be chain nuking and want a pet with higher ac, we have to do with our one and only warder.<br>
<br>
Considering we can tank for our pets when needed and has better heals our warders dont need high ac as much as your earth pets (they dont have that btw, at least not prior to the last patch) but instead need more damage dealing. In fact, for both classes to be as efficient as they can warders should be outdamaging all your pets besides the water pet when the water pet is in back stabbing position and it should be a worse tank than your earth and air pets.<br>
<br>
<br>
If you dont agree you dont agree, you made your point clear and unless I misunderstood what you meant Im not really keen on getting in on a pet vs warder discussion again. We have different needs and my version on what mages is just as biased as your version on what beastlords need. Only someone who played both classes to 60 and doesnt have a favorite/main would be able to make a useful comparsion. I dont know why I even bothered in trying to explain to you why mages and beastlords are equally pet dependent other than its annoying seeing this old thread dragged up again with the same old arguments as have been discussed in absurdum. And the only reason I can think of why it would be done is that Verant is comparing all pet classes on test and is trying to remove the bugs they gave our warder. <p><div align="center"><img src=http://member.isavvix.com/cyberwarlock/images/EQ/DahkarET.jpg border=0 width=197 height=250></div></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/udannorstoutwise.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dannor Stoutwise</A> at: 10/5/02 10:15:28 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub115.ezboard.com/utheneweqman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TheNewEQman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF9933>(10/5/02 10:44:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3675.topic&index=62>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mysupersales.com/mysupersales_468x60.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Mages &amp; Beastlords... what is the best pet?</span><hr size=1> Hate to say it but the mages pet is there class. LOL here is better idea... upgrade the mage pet... AND upgrade beastlord pet. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCOD